u05e9, \u05d1\u05e0\u05d9 \u05d1\u05e8\u05e7 \u05d1\u05de\u05e7\u05d5\u05dd \u05d4\u05e9\u05e0\u05d9: \u05d0\u05dc\u05d5 \u05de\u05d5\u05e7\u05d3\u05d9 \u05d4\u05e7\u05d5\u05e8\u05d5\u05e0\u05d4 \u05d1\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc|language=Hebrew|trans-title=Jerusalem leads, Bnei Brak in 2nd place|first=Boaz|last=Efrat|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=29 March 2020|work=[[Walla!]]}}</ref> is incomplete. As of March 29, 2020, the Ministry of Health does not make the number of cases by city available to the general public.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.haaretz.co.il/health/corona/.premium-1.8716313|title=\u05e4\u05d9 \u05e9\u05de\u05d5\u05e0\u05d4 \u05d1\u05d1\u05e0\u05d9 \u05d1\u05e8\u05e7, \u05e4\u05d9 \u05d0\u05e8\u05d1\u05e2\u05d4 \u05d1\u05d9\u05e8\u05d5\u05e9\u05dc\u05d9\u05dd: \u05d6\u05d9\u05e0\u05d5\u05e7 \u05d1\u05de\u05e1\u05e4\u05e8 \u05d4\u05d7\u05d5\u05dc\u05d9\u05dd \u05d1\u05e8\u05d9\u05db\u05d5\u05d6\u05d9\u05dd \u05d7\u05e8\u05d3\u05d9\u05d9\u05dd|language=Hebrew|trans-title=Eight times the rate in Bnei Brak|first=Aharon|last=Rabinowitz|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=29 March 2020|work=[[Haaretz]]}}</ref>\n# Not included in this data is the death in Italy of one Israeli tourist.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/82-year-old-israeli-tourist-dies-in-italy-after-contracting-coronavirus/|title=82-year-old Israeli tourist dies in Italy after contracting coronavirus|date=28 March 2020|work=Times of Israel|access-date=29 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n*[[2020 in Israel]]\n*[[Health in Israel]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Israel|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n;Government\n*[https://govextra.gov.il/ministry-of-health/corona/corona-virus-en/ The Novel Coronavirus]. Israel's government website\n*[https://www.gov.il/en/General/corona_official Coronavirus information and up