t Miami in 1973, catching for 450 yards on 33 receptions with 9 touchdowns. As a sophomore in 1974 he started all 13 games and had 1,034 yards on 56 receptions with 14 touchdowns.\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football running back}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox NFL player\n|name          = Mark Walton\n|current_team  = Free agent\n|number        = \n|position      = [[Running back]]\n|birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1997|3|29}}\n|birth_place   = [[Miami, Florida]]\n| height_ft    = 5\n| height_in    = 10\n| weight_lb    = 200\n| high_school  = [[Booker T. Washington High School (Miami)|Miami (FL) Booker T. Washington]]\n| college      = [[Miami Hurricanes football|Miami (FL)]]\n| draftyear    = 2018\n| draftround   = 4\n| draftpick    = 112\n| pastteams    =\n* [[Cincinnati Bengals]] ({{NFL Year|2018}})\n* [[Miami Dolphins]] ({{NFL Year|2019}})    \n|status=\n|statweek=\n|statseason=2019\n|statlabel1=[[Rushing yards]]\n|statvalue1=235\n|statlabel2=Rushing average\n|statvalue2=3.5\n|statlabel3=[[Touchdown|Rushing touchdowns]]\n|statvalue3=0\n|statlabel4=[[Reception (American football)|Receptions]]\n|statvalue4=20\n|statlabel5=[[Receiving yards]]\n|statvalue5=130\n|statlabel6=[[Touchdown|Receiving touchdowns]]\n|statvalue6=0\n| nflnew       = markwalton/2560915\n}}\n\n'''Mark Walton''' (born March 29, 1997) is an [[American football]] [[running back]] who is a [[free agent]]. After playing [[college football]] at the [[University of Miami]], he was drafted by the [[Cincinnati Bengals]] in the fourth round of the [[2018 NFL Draft]]. He also played for the [[Miami Dolphins]].\n\n==Early years==\nWalton attended [[Booker T. Washington High School (Miami)|Booker T. Washington High School]] in [[Miami, Florida]]. During his career, he rushed for 2,769 yards and 45 [[touchdowns]] for the Tornadoes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://miamiherald.typepad.com/umiami/2015/01/booker-t-washington-star-running-back-mark-walton-looking-forward-to-becoming-a-hurricane.html |title=Booker T. Washington star running back Mark Walton looking forward to becoming a Hurricane |work=Miami Herald |access-date=October 10, 2018}}</ref> He committed to the [[University of Miami]] to play college football.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/ncfrecruiting/southeast/post/_/id/22335/2016-rb-mark-walton-commits-to-miami |title=2016 RB Mark Walton commits to Miami |last=Dowlar |first=Corey |work=ESPN.com |access-date=October 10, 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/sports/miami-hurricanes/sfl-mark-walton-james-king-sign-with-miami-20150204-story.html |title=Booker T. Washington's Walton, King sign with Miami |last=Chirinos |first=Christy Cabrera |work=Sun-Sentinel.com |access-date=October 10, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nWalton played in all 13 games as a true freshman at Miami in 2015, rushing for 450 yards on 129 carries with 9 touchdowns. As a sophomore in 2016, he started all 13 games and rushed for 1,117 yards on 209 carries with 14 touchdowns.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/sports/college/acc/university-of-miami/article143211824.html |title=UM\u2019s Mark Walton: focused, fierce, excelling amid family struggles |last=Degnan |first=Susan Miller |work=Miami Herald |access-date=October 10, 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://caneswatch.blog.palmbeachpost.com/2016/12/22/mark-walton-in-every-way-the-no-1-back-for-miami-hurricanes-in-2016/ |title=Mark Walton, in every way, the No. 1 back for Miami Hurricanes in 2016 |last=Porter |first=Matt |work=Palm Beach Post |access-date=October 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/sports/miami-hurricanes/fl-um-football-1222-20161221-story.html |title=After year of ups and downs, Mark Walton heads into bowl game as UM's MVP |last=Chirinos |first=Christy Cabrera |work=Sun-Sentinel.com |access-date=October 10, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> In 2017, as a junior, he rushed for 428 yards and three touchdowns on 56 carries in only four games due to ankle surgery which forced him to miss a majority of the season.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/sports/college/acc/university-of-miami/article210023784.html |title=Who is Mark Walton, the Miami Hurricanes running back drafted by the Cincinnati Bengals? |last=Degnan |first=Susan Miller |work=Miami Herald |access-date=October 10, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On December 5, 2017, Walton declared his intentions to enter the [[2018 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/sports/miami-hurricanes/fl-sp-hurricanes-mark-walton-draft-20171205-story.html |title=Hurricanes star running back Mark Walton declares for the 2018 NFL draft |last=Davis |first=Craig |access-date=December 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Collegiate statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami Hurricanes|color=white}}\"| Mark Walton\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align: center; font-weight:bold;\" | Rushing\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align: center; font-weight:bold;\" | Receiving\n|-\n| '''Year'''\n| '''School'''\n| '''Conf'''\n| '''Class'''\n| '''Pos'''\n| '''G'''\n| '''Att'''\n| '''Yds'''\n| '''Avg'''\n| '''TD'''\n| '''Rec'''\n| '''Yds'''\n| '''Avg'''\n| '''TD'''\n|-\n| [[2015 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2015]]\n| [[2015 Miami Hurricanes football team|Miami (FL)]]\n| [[2015 Atlantic Coast Conference football season|ACC]]\n| FR\n| RB\n| 13\n| 130\n| 461\n| 3.5\n| 9\n| 22\n| 293\n| 13.3\n| 1\n|-\n| [[2016 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2016]]\n| [[2016 Miami Hurricanes football team|Miami (FL)]]\n| [[2016 Atlantic Coast Conference football season|ACC]]\n| SO\n| RB\n| 13\n| 209\n| 1,117\n| 5.3\n| 14\n| 27\n| 240\n| 8.9\n| 1\n|-\n| [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2017]]\n| [[2017 Miami Hurricanes football team|Miami (FL)]]\n| [[2017 Atlantic Coast Conference football season|ACC]]\n| JR\n| RB\n| 5\n| 56\n| 428\n| 7.6\n| 3\n| 7\n| 91\n| 13.0\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | Career\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | Miami (FL)\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | \n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 31\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 395\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 2,006\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 5.1\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 26\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 56\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 624\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 11.1\n| style=\"font-weight:bold;\" | 2\n|}\n\n==Professional career==\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 5\n|    height in = 9\u215d\n|       weight = 202\n|         dash = 4.60\n|    ten split =\n| twenty split =\n|      shuttle =\n|   cone drill =\n|     vertical = 31.5\n|     broad ft = 9\n|     broad in = 10\n|        bench = 18\n|     arm span = 30\n|    hand span = 9\u00bc\n|    wonderlic =\n|         note = All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/mark-walton?id=32195741-4c80-8914-fd4d-6ca747e909bd |title=Mark Walton Combine Profile |website=NFL.com |access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref> \n}}\n\n===Cincinnati Bengals===\nWalton was drafted by the [[Cincinnati Bengals]] in the fourth round (112th overall) of the [[2018 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000929813/article/cincinnati-bengals-draft-rb-mark-walton-at-no-112 |title=Cincinnati Bengals draft RB Mark Walton at No. 112 |last=Teope, Herbie |date=April 28, 2018 |website=NFL.com |access-date=May 6, 2018}}</ref> In the Bengals' Week 4 victory over the [[2018 Atlanta Falcons|Atlanta Falcons]], he had his first five professional carries for nine rushing yards to go along with two receptions for 28 receiving yards.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/201809300atl.htm |title=Cincinnati Bengals at Atlanta Falcons - September 30th, 2018 |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=October 10, 2018}}</ref> Overall, he finished his rookie season with 14 carries for 34 rushing yards to go along with five receptions for 41 receiving yards.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/W/WaltMa00/gamelog/2018/ |title=Mark Walton 2018 Game Log |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=March 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2019, Walton was waived by the Bengals after being arrested for the third time in the offseason.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cincyjungle.com/2019/4/6/18298234/bengals-waive-rb-mark-walton |title=Bengals waive RB Mark Walton |date=April 6, 2019 |website=CincyJungle.com}}</ref>\n\n===Miami Dolphins===\nAfter a mini-camp tryout, Walton signed with the [[Miami Dolphins]] on May 12, 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.miamidolphins.com/news/dolphins-sign-kirk-barron-jamar-summers-mark-walton |title=Dolphins Sign Kirk Barron, Jamar Summers & Mark Walton |date=May 12, 2019 |access-date=May 12, 2019 |website=MiamiDolphins.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190512221755/https://www.miamidolphins.com/news/dolphins-sign-kirk-barron-jamar-summers-mark-walton |archive-date=May 12, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Walton made his first start against the [[2019 Washington Redskins season|Washington Redskins]], rushing six times for 32 yards in a 16\u201317 Dolphins loss. He rushed for 66 yards on 14 carries the following week against the [[2019 Buffalo Bills season|Buffalo Bills]], also catching one reception for -8 yards.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/dolphins-mark-walton-paces-backfield-in-loss/ |title=Dolphins' Mark Walton: Paces backfield in loss |date=October 20, 2019 |website=CBSSports.com |language=en}}</ref> On November 4, he was suspended four games by the NFL for violating the league's personal conduct and substance abuse policies for his offseason arrests.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/28008434/dolphins-rb-mark-walton-suspended-four-games-three-offseason-arrests |title=Dolphins RB Mark Walton suspended four games for three offseason arrests |last=Wolfe |first=Cameron |date=November 4, 2019 |access-date=November 4, 2019 |website=ESPN.com}}</ref> He was waived on November 19, 2019 for a police issue.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.miamidolphins.com/news/miami-dolphins-waive-mark-walton |title=Miami Dolphins Waive Mark Walton |date=November 19, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019 |website=MiamiDolphins.com}}</ref> His suspension was lifted on December 3, 2019.<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1201986759866888192 |user=AaronWilson_NFL |title=Former Dolphins RB Mark Walton suspension lifted remains a free agent |date=December 3, 2019 |access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Legal issues==\nWalton was arrested three times during the 2019 off-season. He was first arrested and charged with misdemeanor marijuana possession on January 16, 2019, in North Miami-Dade.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://bengalswire.usatoday.com/2019/02/18/mark-walton-unreported-january-arrest/ |title=Report: Mark Walton had unreported January arrest |last=Roling, Chris |date=February 18, 2019 |access-date=January 3, 2020 |website=USAToday.com}}</ref> On February 15, 2019, he was arrested for a second time and charged with misdemeanor battery for an altercation triggered after he grabbed a phone from a neighbor in Miami.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/crime/article226380530.html |title=Mark Walton, former Canes star now with the Cincinnati Bengals, arrested in Miami |last=Ovalle, David |date=February 16, 2019 |access-date=January 3, 2020 |website=MiamiHerald.com}}</ref> The charges underlying his third arrest on April 4, 2019, stemmed from a March 12, 2019, incident in which Walton fled on foot from his rented car after police tried to pull him over. Authorities found a rifle in the car and accused Walton of carrying a concealed firearm, resisting an officer without violence, possession of marijuana, and reckless driving.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.upi.com/Sports_News/NFL/2019/04/04/Bengals-RB-Mark-Walton-arrested-for-third-time-in-2019-hit-with-police-Taser/4431554394353/ |title=Bengals RB Mark Walton arrested for third time in 2019, hit with police Taser |last=Butler, Alex |date=April 4, 2019 |access-date=January 3, 2020 |website=UPI.com}}</ref> Walton pleaded no contest to a misdemeanor weapons charge from the March 2019 incident on August 19, 2019, and he received six months of probation and was required to turn in all of his firearms as well as undergo anger management and driving courses.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001042824/article/dolphins-rb-mark-walton-gets-6-months-probation |title=Dolphins RB Mark Walton gets 6 months probation |date=August 19, 2019 |access-date=January 3, 2020 |website=NFL.com}}</ref>\n\nOn November 19, 2019, Walton was arrested in [[Davie, Florida]], for allegedly attacking a woman who was five months pregnant with his child. Walton was charged with aggravated battery of a pregnant person.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/19/sports/football/mark-walton-arrest-dolphins.html |title=Dolphins Cut Mark Walton After Battery Arrest |date=November 19, 2019 |access-date=November 19, 2019 |website=NYTimes.com}}</ref> On January 3, 2020, he was charged with a second count of aggravated battery of a pregnant woman for a different incident with the same woman in March 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/28415168/ex-dolphins-rb-mark-walton-faces-2nd-domestic-assault-accusation |title=Ex-Fins RB faces 2nd domestic assault accusation |date=January 3, 2020 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=January 3, 2020}}</ref> He was arrested on February 27, 2020, for violating a restraining order.<ref>{{cite news |author=Alexander, Christina |title=Former UM, Dolphins player Mark Walton arrested |url=https://wsvn.com/sports/former-um-dolphins-player-mark-walton-arrested/ |website=WSVN.com |date=February 27, 2020 |accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://hurricanesports.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=5595 Miami Hurricanes bio]\n*[https://www.bengals.com/team/players-roster/mark-walton/ Cincinnati Bengals bio]\n*{{twitter|_Hungry_1}}\n\n{{Bengals2018DraftPicks}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Walton, Mark}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Miami]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Florida]]\n[[Category:American football running backs]]\n[[Category:Miami Hurricanes football players]]\n[[Category:Cincinnati Bengals players]]\n[[Category:Miami Dolphins players]]\n", "name_user": "Louis992", "label": "safe", "comment": "False information", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Walton_(American_football)"}
